title: Aggregated catch of tuna and tuna-like species in the Atlantic and Indian oceans (%year_start%-%year_end%) by french surface fisheries – logbook data (by Exclusive Economic Zone and latitude / %parameter_temporal_resolution% %parameter_temporal_resolution_unit%)
description:
This dataset lists the spatially and temporally aggregated catch of tuna and tuna-like species (i.e. billfish, bonitos, and mackerel) in the Atlantic and Indian oceans made by french surface fisheries from %year_start% to %year_end%. Species-specific catches expressed in weight or number are stratified by fishing gear, vessel flag reporting country, fate of catch, fishing mode (i.e. type of school used), time (regular steps of %parameter_temporal_resolution%%parameter_temporal_resolution_unit%) and area (statistical squares of %parameter_grid_spatial_resolution%° longitude and latitude).

These data were collected by the Observatory of Exploited Tropical Pelagic Ecosystems (Ob7) of the French National Research Institute for Sustainable Development (IRD). They were extracted from the Balbaya database. Balbaya database gathers the fine (i.e. exact spatial location and time) data collated from logbooks for purse seine and pole-and-line vessel from french surface tuna fisheries and partners. This database contains data about landings, individual sample and corrections of catches and fishing efforts by set.

To produce this dataset, fine data (i.e. exact spatial location and date) were aggregated on a %parameter_temporal_resolution%%parameter_temporal_resolution_unit% timeframe and %parameter_grid_spatial_resolution%° longitude and latitude resolution grid. More details on the processes are provided in the lineage section.
supplemental_information:
- EEZ polygons are extracted from MarineRegions website (v9) (http://marineregions.org/)

title: Aggregated catch of tuna and tuna-like species in the Atlantic and Indian oceans (%year_start%-%year_end%) for french surface fisheries collected by the onboard observers (temporal resolution : %parameter_temporal_resolution% %parameter_temporal_resolution_unit% ; spatial resolution : statistical squares of %parameter_grid_spatial_resolution%° longitude and latitude)
description: This dataset lists catch of tuna and tuna-like species in the Atlantic and Indian oceans for french surface fisheries from %year_start% to %year_end% aggregated on a %parameter_grid_spatial_resolution% degrees and %parameter_temporal_resolution% %parameter_temporal_resolution_unit% grid resolution (observers and logbooks). These data come from Observe database and are collected by French National Research Institute for Sustainable Development (IRD). Observe database gathers the fine data for seine and longline vessel from french surface tuna fisheries and partners. This database contains data come from observers embarked upon a vessel and are about discarded, bycatch and thier features. This database can contains incorrect data, a correction of database is make manually. The processing uses only fishing activities from DCF IRD and TAAF, Moratoir 2013+ and OCUP programs. Moreover, auto-sample commercial trips are not include. For longline sets, the centroid and the hauling start time are used to combine to spatiotemporal resolution. The processing uses only fishing activities.

T3plus database gathers the fine data for seine and pole-and-line vessel from french surface tuna fisheries and partners. This database allows to correct catch data and forcast size samples.
